	<!-- changes made for 2.1
		1. rearranged to bring together sections related to same Fedora function
		2. little or no change to servlet and servlet-mapping sections
		3. much change to security-constraints to tighten container security for those urls and methods
		not otherwise specifically declared
		4. several security-constraints may still be at odds with client code not yet 
		sending credentials; see to-do below 
	-->
	
	<!-- to do: 
		1. implement basic auth in client code which accesses some urls.
		Fedora < 2.1 has credentials passed and detected in a variety of ad hoc ways, 
		including writing and reading password in querystring,
		reading http headers directly (web.xml wasn't correct to force tomcat to do this for POSTs),
		user=fedoraAdmin assumed (hardcoded) at server.
		2. we have only one web resource name == Fedora Management Interface.
		having only one seems appropriate, but the chosen name is misleadingly specific;
		should we change it?  any implications?
		3. the servlet names (labels) and display names could be regularized; may be too late/messy now.
		4. /mgmt/getNextPID not formed generally, e.g., /management/upload; should we use /management/getNextPID ?
		5. note:  the explicit login servlet has become essentially an upfront authentication ping.  xacml authz is 
		not involved, as servlet does not call fedora internals
	-->

